Goran is an ordinary taxi driver in Bogovaða, Serbia.
His taxi is not very good - the starter engine is pulling its last and has seen its best days anyway.
However, the most important thing for Goran's customers is that the taxi moves at all, and that it moves towards the Hungarian border.
Bogovaða is a small village of 500 inhabitants, about 60 kilometers southwest of Belgrade.
Next to the village there is a centre for asylum seekers, where mainly families are admitted.
