They are told to hide among the vegetation and wait for a sign.
When it is given, it is necessary to board the ship quickly.
Passengers must remain hidden under deck all the way.
The Coast Guard can only observe how deep the ship is swimming, as there are no other signs of crowding.
Food and drink are given, but the less passengers defecate and vomit, the better.
Küçük receives approximately €53,000 for one luxury boat trip after expenses.
He doesn't take care of the practicalities himself, but hires captains, recruiters, security guards, hosts and other smaller workers to do the work for him.
During the summer season, at least hundreds of shipments are arranged and Küçük earns millions.
Through front companies, he is believed to have bought land, a pharmaceutical company and more than a hundred apartments that he rents.
In 2011, Muammer Küçük was arrested at the same time as a member of parliament from the Turkish Democratic Party and a pharmaceutical entrepreneur.
